<br>
Ephiny, I have come to speak to you a promise from my heart.<br>
::she glances as she sees a lone falcon fly overhead...crying as if it is singing to the soul of the lost amazon::<br>
<br>
Athelfi, I have not known you as well as I would have liked to.  Tho in our encounters at Council meetings, Battles, and few times as athelfi.  I grew in great respect for you as an athelfi and warrior.  I know within in you resided the hope that one day the scattered tribes of the Amazons would become a great Nation once again.  I, too, have had that deep desire.  I remember those days when we where the incredible Amazon Nations.  We were feared and respected.  Proud women who needed no one but ourselves.  The Battle that occured here will not be forgotten.  I promise.  <br>
::Hipp grows silent and fights a tear, that comes to surface and twinkles in the sunlight that beams between the clouds.  Hipp looks up at the clouds, as the wind begins to grow strong and her auburn hair blows carelessly with it.  Her brown eyes watch as the clouds above move in a feverish dance across the sky...she bends down and softly touches the ground with with her finger tips.  Then she reaches up to take the golden horse pendant that lies upon her breast and rips it from her neck.  Then places it upon the ground that holds Amazon blood.:::<br>
You will not be forgotten, athelfi. <br>
::she stands and puts a fisted hand to her chest:: No Amazon who has laid their blood on this ground will be forgotten!<br>
::she sighs deeply and then turns to walk towards her mare.  Then stops.. glances back at the spot:: <br>
I promise!<br>
